  <hr />

  <h2>User Interviews & Discovery</h2>
  <p>
    In order to understand and analyze the ways SoundCloud was used, I conducted
    interviews over Zoom and Discord with target demographics to discover key
    information I was looking for.
  </p>
  <h3>Interview details</h3>

  <div class="callout-inverted">
    <h3>
    Interiewee criteria: 
    </h3>
    <p>Those who have previous experience in using SoundCloud's
    mobile app</p>
    
    <h3>
    Research objectives:<br /></h3>
    <p>
    To uncover primary usage of the app<br />
    To learn about types of activities conducted on the app<br />
    Finding design opportunities based on activities conducted leading up to the
    usage of the app
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>
Insights    </h3>
  <img
    src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1642579525/Frame_4_hf5lfm.png"
  />
  <!-- <img
    src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1642579525/Slide_16_9_-_1_zhhxim.png"
  /> -->
  <p>
    <small>A summary of key insights from interviews.</small>
  </p>
  <p>
    A primary use case amongst
    interviewees included listening to <strong>instrumental soundtracks</strong>
    while they conducted their day-to-day tasks such as studying or doing their chores.
    Their issue with this was that while they open SoundCloud when they intend to
    be productive, they may
    <strong
      >unintentionally leave the app when they get distracted from their task.</strong
    >, at which point the music stops playing. This lead to my problem
    statement:
  </p>

    <h3 class="callout">
      How might we minimize the chances of users <strong>unintentionally stopping their
      music?</strong>
    </h3>
  <!-- <img
    src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1642579525/Frame_4_hf5lfm.png"
  />
  <p>
    <small
      >A user persona based upon issues and goals discovered during interviews.</small
    >
  </p> -->
  <div class="grid-twocol">
    <h2>Pitch</h2>
    <p>
      Seeing that outside distractions seemed to be the leading obstacle in user
      retention, I decided a fun way to prevent this issue was by proposing a <strong
        >focus timer</strong
      > feature. This would work so that users are able to combine one of their pre-existing
      playlists with a count-down timer so that they are
      <strong
        >encouraged to retain their focus for a set amount of time, therefore
        minimizing their likelihood of leaving the app</strong
      > due to distractions.
    </p>
  </div>
  <br />
  <img
    src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1642579525/Frame_5_vcqqum.png"
  />
  <p>
    <small
      >Titled "focus mode", made to address the problems felt by the user
      persona.</small
    >
  </p>

  <div class="grid-twocol">
    <h2>Prototype</h2>
    <p>
      I created three rounds of wireframes for the focus timer in the span of
      one week, from low fidelity to high. Throughout the process, I was able to
      get feedback from my peers as to what parts of the interaction were
      unclear to them, which helped in identifying interactions I should focus
      on iterating upon.
    </p>
